FBIS3-20361 "drweu061_l_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-061 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 SPAIN One Killed, Two Injured in Vitoria Bomb Blast LD2903071694 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 0800 GMT 29 Mar 94 LD2903071694 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] One person died and another two were slightly injured last night in Vitoria when a bomb exploded in the city center. The blast also caused substantial physical damage in the area. The civil government has confirmed that the deceased is the young man who was carrying the device. Maria Jesus Iparaguirre is at the scene: [Iparaguirre] [Passage omitted] The area is still cordonned off and the remains of the body, somebody who apparently was carrying or handling the device, are still here. According to Cesar Milano, the civil governor and the acting governmant delegate, the device could have comprised 15 or 20 kilos of amonal or amosal and shrapnel. Therefore, the target could have been a member of the state security forces. The incident occurred around 0520. [passage omitted] Approximately 20 cars and 60 dwellings have been affected. This is a shopping area and many shops have had their windows and interiors completely destroyed. [passge omitted]
